content.text:
The issue was that `CardTemplatePreviewer` did not correctly map the provided `mOrdinal` (which represents the card's `ord`) to the `cardIndex` (the index in the list of available cards for the note) when launched from the `NoteEditor`. This caused the preview to always show the first card of the note, regardless of which card was selected in the browser or editor.

For standard notes, the `ord` is typically the same as the index. However, for cloze notes, the `ord` corresponds to the cloze number (minus one), and since not all cloze numbers might be present in a note (e.g., `{{c1::}}` and `{{c3::}}` without `{{c2::}}`), the index in the list of generated cards is not necessarily equal to the `ord`.

I have implemented the following changes in `CardTemplatePreviewer.kt`:
1.  Added a helper method `indexFromOrdinal(col, ordinal, fieldValues)` that correctly calculates the `cardIndex` from the `mOrdinal` by looking up the cloze number in the generated cards for cloze notes, or using the `ordinal` directly for standard notes.
2.  Updated `onCollectionLoaded` to initialize `cardIndex` using this helper method when `mNoteEditorBundle` is present.
3.  Ensured that the navigation buttons (Previous/Next) have their enabled/disabled states correctly set upon the initial load of the previewer.

These changes ensure that the previewer starts on the expected card and that navigation works correctly from the start.

### Changes:

#### `AnkiDroid/src/main/java/com/ichi2/anki/CardTemplatePreviewer.kt`

- Modified `onCollectionLoaded` to set `cardIndex` based on `mOrdinal` and fields from `mNoteEditorBundle`.
- Added `indexFromOrdinal` private method to handle the mapping from `ord` to `cardIndex`.
- Updated navigation button state initialization in `onCollectionLoaded`.

```kotlin
    override fun onCollectionLoaded(col: Collection) {
        super.onCollectionLoaded(col)
        if (mNoteEditorBundle != null) {
            mAllFieldsNull = false
            // loading from the note editor
            val fieldValues = getBundleEditFields(mNoteEditorBundle)
            cardIndex = indexFromOrdinal(col, mOrdinal, fieldValues)
            val toPreview = setCurrentCardFromNoteEditorBundle(col)
            if (toPreview != null) {
                cardCount = toPreview.note().numberOfCardsEphemeral()
                if (cardCount >= 2) {
                    previewLayout!!.showNavigationButtons()
                    previewLayout!!.setPrevButtonEnabled(isPrevBtnEnabled(cardIndex))
                    previewLayout!!.setNextButtonEnabled(isNextBtnEnabled(cardIndex))
                }
            }
        } else {
            // ... (rest of the method)
        }
        // ...
    }

    private fun indexFromOrdinal(col: Collection, ordinal: Int, fieldValues: List<String>): Int {
        val notetype = mEditedNotetype ?: return ordinal
        if (notetype.isCloze) {
            val n = col.newNote(notetype)
            for (i in fieldValues.indices) {
                if (i < n.fields.size) {
                    n.setField(i, fieldValues[i])
                }
            }
            val clozeNumbers = col.clozeNumbersInNote(n)
            val index = clozeNumbers.indexOf(ordinal + 1)
            return if (index != -1) index else 0
        }
        return ordinal
    }
```

This fix addresses the reported bug where the preview showed the wrong card when opened from the "Edit Note" screen.

